The aim of the course is to give an overview of different types of nanostructured materials, their main properties and applications, as well as production methods. The course covers physical, chemical, biological and technological aspects of the material science at nanoscale. The most important nanomaterials like e.g. carbon nanotubes are discussed in more details. The students are also welcomed to visit laboratories dealing with nanoscience and nanotechnology.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of different nanostructural materials, their properties and applications.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course students are expected to be familiar with most common types of nanostructured materials, to know their main properties and application as well as to understand some important phenomena at nanoscale.
